Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.02,0:00:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This fixture begins with a clear voice and enough silence for the detector to settle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.68,0:00:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each caption line uses ordinary words so subtitle synchronization can focus on timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.82,0:00:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third sentence is intentionally longer and gives the alignment code a wider speech island.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.63,0:00:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After a pause the speaker continues with another compact sentence for the next cue.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.77,0:00:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A reliable fixture needs variation in length without becoming a long audiobook.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.12,0:00:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This cue mentions video containers audio codecs and subtitle rewrites in plain language.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.41,0:00:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next phrase arrives after silence so the voice activity detector can split the span.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.99,0:00:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Short captions still matter because real subtitle files often mix brief and longer lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.98,0:00:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another sentence adds more timing evidence before the final codec cases begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.27,0:01:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Near the end we keep the same calm delivery and leave room for timing drift checks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.43,0:01:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One more cue gives the stretch test a broader timeline across the fixture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.36,0:01:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The final spoken cue closes the fixture with a simple sentence and a clean ending.
